README
======

jQuery Plugin inspired by Lancelot for KDE no-click interface.

Automatically go to the link only with hover, no need to click!


Example
=======
See the demo for more.


	$('.lancelot').lancelot({
		hoverTime: 2000,			//time to launch the link
		aclass: "lancelotGo",		//style, see lancelot.css
		atext: "hover here!",		//text to show
		show: "false",				//
		display: "inline",			//inline, block ...
		speed: "fast",				//animation
		linkAction: "_blank",		//open, _blank or none
		atitle: "go in 2s",			//link title
		alink: "http://example.com" //url OR function or none
	});


Advanced
--------
You can pass a function to "alink", example:

	var googleSearch = function(){
		//obj is a reference to each $('.lancelot')
		return "http://google.com/#q="+obj.text()
	};

	$('.lancelot').lancelot({
		alink: googleSearch
	});

This will create a link to google search with the text from $('.lancelot').

See this working on http://ttlocal.info



